scope & rights:
  Deliberately bounded to the two books read — The Assassin's Blade (the five novellas)
  and Throne of Glass (book one). The rest of the series and the wider Maas universe are
  left out by design, to be catalogued when read. Personas are written strictly to book-one
  knowledge and adversarially checked to strip later-book spoilers.
  The works and characters are © Sarah J. Maas. The personas are catalogued personifications
  under the DLW standard — bibliographic commentary, not original creations. Credit for the
  catalogue returns to the human governor.

